{
  "texts": [
    "They mentioned that, in the finance domain, cost of producing human labeled data is harder and expensive due to challenges around regulations, privacy and availability of humans with specialized knowledge.",
    "C. Computation costsThe two major contributors to computational costs are training cost and inference cost.",
    "Computational costs associated with training Gen-AI models from the ground up can easily run into billions of dollars [36].",
    "However, Xia et al. [36] noted that fine tuning III-B can help reduce this cost for certain applications.Inference cost associated with the integration of Gen-AI workflows will be high considering the billions of stock market trades, credit card payment and banking transactions within a day [37].",
    "Further, pricing models of Gen-AI APIs available for commercial use vary from $5 to $15 per million input tokens."
  ]
}